GUI Interface Improvement To-Do Checklist
This checklist is based on the current live GUI suggested to be used by Member 1 to refine the interface.
High priority
[ ] Replace the current `Record Type + Action` workflow with a clearer task structure.
[ ] Change the `Execute` button to a context-specific label such as `Create Client`, `Search Client`, `Update Flight`, or `Delete Airline`.
[ ] Hide or disable controls that do not match the current context.
[ ] Rename `Input Form` dynamically so it matches the selected task.
[ ] Improve the `Results` area so it presents output clearly.
[ ] Add clear success and error feedback after each action.
[ ] Add stronger input validation for required fields, IDs, phone numbers, ZIP code, and dates.
Medium priority
[ ] Group fields into logical sections such as identity, address, and contact details.
[ ] Mark required and optional fields clearly.
[ ] Improve spacing, alignment, and consistency across all forms.
[ ] Add inline guidance for fields with strict formats.
[ ] Allow easier record selection for update and delete tasks.
[ ] Show search results in a structured table or list where possible.
[ ] Add a status line for useful context such as last action or record count.
Accessibility improvements
[ ] Increase contrast between the background, labels, inputs, and buttons.
[ ] Ensure keyboard focus is visible.
[ ] Improve keyboard navigation order.
[ ] Make controls large enough for comfortable interaction.
[ ] Keep field labels clear and persistent.
[ ] Make error messages specific and easy to understand.
Usability improvements
[ ] Reduce the number of decisions required at the start of the workflow.
[ ] Support recognition over recall by helping users browse or select records.
[ ] Make the most common actions more obvious.
[ ] Improve visual hierarchy so the next step is easy to understand.
[ ] Apply a cleaner and more consistent visual style.
Suggested implementation order
Improve the main workflow and task structure.
Replace `Execute` with task-specific action labels.
Make controls context-sensitive.
Improve validation and feedback.
Redesign the results area.
Improve accessibility and keyboard support.
Refine layout, grouping, and visual consistency.
